Guardian Gets $82 Million Dividend From Auto Traders, Times Says

-- B y   F i r a t   K a y a k i r a n
-- 
2011-08-07T07:38:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-07/guardian-gets-82-million-dividend-from-auto-traders-times-says.html
The Guardian Media Group Plc, owner
of the Guardian and Observer newspapers, received 50 million
pounds ($82 million) in dividends from its stake in Auto Traders
magazine, the Sunday Times reported, without saying where it got
the information.  The group will use the sum to help fund declining revenues
in its newspaper business, the Sunday Times said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Firat Kayakiran in London at 
 fkayakiran@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
